I was asked to make an all-archer goblin unit, and it instantly took me back to when I first started collecting goblins for Warhammer. Back then, my assistant lecturer’s salary didn’t leave much room for the hobby, so I was over the moon to find an eBay lot of a hundred goblin archers going for pennies. That bargain became my very first goblin archer unit — a proper horde of those classic monopose Kev Adams sculpts, all grinning the same grin, all ready to rain arrows (and probably trip over each other).

This little project was just for the sake of reliving those memories — don’t worry, I’ll be making a proper unit of goblin archers too.

Hello everyone,
The Advent season is all about joy and giving, and I think it's just part of it to give others a little joy.

First of all, I would like to sincerely thank everyone who has supported me on Patreon over the past few years. Without your support, I probably wouldn't have taken the time to create some of my miniatures. It was a great motivation that helped me move forward - thank you so much!
But the time on Patreon has passed due to a lack of time. The fact that you have the opportunity to download these old publications today is primarily thanks to them.

<b>MyLinks: https://allmylinks.com/enfenix</b>

---
<p>General information</p>

My miniatures are designed to work out of the box with original 28mm Hero Quest miniatures.
I always add a version with Heroquest base and one without a base. The weapons and the base are only combined (if possible). If you need different HeroQuest-style base, you should check out my customizer:
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4299465

Personally, I now prefer 32mm miniatures. I usually scale them to 112% -115% directly in the slicer.

I am happy about every shared make, especially the painted ones.
By the way i love espresso, so don't hesitate to leave a tip if you like =D

If you are inexperienced with slicer setting, I recommend this one for ...
Ender 3: https://www.fatdragongames.com/fdgfiles/cura-ender-3-5-profiles-work-cr-10/
Bambu A1 Printer: https://www.fatdragongames.com/fdgfiles/bambu-studio-slicer-profiles-a1-mini-3d-printer/

Recently bought some second hand Ogors for AOS to play some Spearhead but felt they needed more bits on them showing their spoils of war as well as a custom gnoblar keg carrier so here's what I came up with.

 Putting these all up for free because of all the support but feel free to add a tip to the open price every bit helps me make more stuff, thank you all.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

The Chest has a notch out of it to allow it to attach to the back of an Ogor model more easily as intended.

 The Gnoblar Keg Carrier was modeled to fit underneath the Ogors carrying the cannons.


---------------------------------------------------------------------

 Update November 5th: Added Shoulder armor bits to the listing.

 Updated November 6th: Added some more bits for use on the backs of Leadbelchers.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

Also big thanks to those who download, knowing you guys are going to enjoy this gives me the drive to make more stuff.

I hope to try to make some more variants.

This pack contains 12 unique strips of goblins for 10mm wargaming like warmasters or similar games. If your building a Orc & Goblin army this is a cheap alternative to the goblins. Six goblins are on every strip, so you get the feeling of a horde of goblins per stand

Included are 12 strips in total
2 command strips for spear goblins
3 spear goblin strips
2 command strips for goblin archers
3 goblin archer strips
2 mixed spear archer goblin strips

The goblins are around 6 - 6.5mm tall to to there eyes in height.

These are intended for resin printing and should be printed without supports direct on the print bead.


Some detail shown in the pictures will not show on the printed model if not scaled up as most consumer printers cant reach that level of detail.
